The paper deals with model checking of probabilistic systems, which involves symbolic manipulation of decision diagrams. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures to efficiently store and manipulate large sets of states, which could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of iterative algorithms and symbolic manipulation of probabilities, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of complex systems, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
